'''Mohamed Elias Achouri''' ({{langx|ar|مُحَمَّد إِلْيَاس عَاشُورِيّ}}; born 10 February 1999) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Danish Superliga]] club [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]]. Born in [[Réunion]], an [[Overseas departments and regions of France|overseas department of France]], he plays for the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].

==Club career==
On 26 August 2021, Achouri joined [[Liga Portugal 2]] club [[C.D. Trofense|Trofense]] on loan from [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[C.D. Trofense|Trofense]]|url=https://cdtrofense.pt/elias-achouri-e-reforco/|title=Elias Achouri é Reforço|date=26 August 2021|accessdate=29 September 2021|language=pt|archive-date=7 September 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230907104954/https://cdtrofense.pt/elias-achouri-e-reforco/|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 31 August 2022, Achouri joined [[Danish Superliga]] side [[Viborg FF]] on a deal until June 2025.<ref>[https://www.vff.dk/nyhed/sport/13305-vff-henter-tunesisk-landsholdsspiller VFF henter tunesisk landsholdsspiller], vff.dk, 31 August 2022</ref>

Achouri made the move to 15-time Danish Superliga champions [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]] on 24 July 2023, signing a four-year deal with the Lions. This was at the time the biggesst sale of Viborg FF ever.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://bold.dk/fodbold/stillinger/superligaen/nyheder/avis-fck-betaler-22-millioner-for-achouri |title=Avis: FCK betaler 22 millioner for Achuri|publisher=bold.dk|date=24 July 2023|language=da}}</ref>

==International career==
Achouri was born in [[Saint-Denis, Réunion|Saint-Denis]], [[Réunion]] to a Tunisian father and an Algerian mother.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.footmercato.net/a3485999445446560247-info-fm-a-la-decouverte-delias-achouri-jeune-etoile-montante-du-vitoria-guimaraes|title=Info FM : à la découverte d'Elias Achouri, jeune étoile montante du Vitoria Guimaraes|website=Foot Mercato : Info Transferts Football - Actu Foot Transfert|date=15 April 2018 }}</ref> He debuted for the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]] in a 4–0 win over [[Equatorial Guinea national football team|Equatorial Guinea]] on 2 June 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/06/02/africa/africa-cup-of-nations-qualification/tunisia/equatorial-guinea/3783068/|title=Tunisia vs. Equatorial Guinea - 2 June 2022 |website=Soccerway}}</ref>

